ðŸ”¹ Parameter Expansion in Bash
Definition:
Parameter Expansion in Bash is a mechanism to manipulate the value of variables when they are expanded using ${...}.
It provides default values, substring extraction, search & replace, case modification, and more.

1. Basic Expansion
name="Rakesh"
echo $name        # Rakesh
echo ${name}      # Rakesh
âœ… ${var} is safer than $var, especially when appending text:
echo "$nameJha"     # will try to expand $nameJha (wrong)
echo "${name}Jha"   # expands $name + "Jha" â†’ RakeshJha

2. Default Values

a) Use Default if Unset
echo ${user:-Guest}
If $user is unset/empty â†’ prints Guest
Else â†’ prints $user

b) Assign Default if Unset
echo ${user:=Guest}
If $user is unset/empty â†’ assigns Guest to $user, then prints it

c) Error if Unset
echo ${user:?Variable not set
If $user is unset/empty â†’ prints error message and exits

d) Alternative Value
echo ${user:+Exists}
If $user is set â†’ prints "Exists"
If unset â†’ prints nothing

3. String Length
name="Rakesh"
echo ${#name}   # 6

4. Substring Extraction
text="HelloWorld"
echo ${text:0:5}   # Hello   (start=0, length=5)
echo ${text:5}     # World   (start=5 till end)

5. Substring Removal

a) Remove Prefix
path="/home/rakesh/docs/file.txt"
echo ${path#*/}   # home/rakesh/docs/file.txt  (shortest match from start)
echo ${path##*/}  # file.txt                  (longest match from start)

b) Remove Suffix
echo ${path%/*}   # /home/rakesh/docs   (shortest match from end)
echo ${path%%/*}  # (empty)             (longest match from end)

6. Search and Replace
fruit="apple banana apple"
echo ${fruit/apple/orange}   # orange banana apple   (first match only)
echo ${fruit//apple/orange}  # orange banana orange  (all matches)

Replace at beginning:
echo ${fruit/#apple/orange}  # orange banana apple

Replace at end:
echo ${fruit/%apple/orange}  # apple banana orange

7. Case Modification (Bash â‰¥ 4)
word="linux"
echo ${word^}    # Linux   (capitalize first letter)
echo ${word^^}   # LINUX   (all uppercase)
echo ${word,}    # linux   (lowercase first letter)
echo ${word,,}   # linux   (all lowercase)

8. Indirection (Indirect Reference)
var="name"
name="Rakesh"
echo ${!var}     # Rakesh   (expands to value of variable whose name is stored in var)

